ear contribution of specific policies to poverty. This is the first book to examine poverty in Europe within the international framework agreed at the 1995 World Summit on Social Development. Breadline Europe provides up-to-date, essential reading for social science undergraduates and postgraduate students. It will also be of considerable interest to policy makers and NGOs with a concern for poverty reduction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aMarginality, SocialvCongresses. 0aMarginality, Social. 0aPovertyvCongresses. 0aPovertyvCross-cultural studies. 0aPovertyxResearchxMethodology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aBaudot, Jaques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradshaw, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurchardt, Tania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDziewiecka-Bokun, Ludmila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerge, Zsuzsa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHalleröd, Björn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangmore, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLayte, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevitas, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLindqvist, Markku, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNolan, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1